
Due to a bug in ubutnu:  
sudo apt-get install ruby-dev ruby-mkrf ruby2.0 ruby2.0-dev
sudo ln -sf /usr/bin/ruby2.0 /usr/bin/ruby
sudo ln -sf /usr/bin/gem2.0 /usr/bin/gem
sudo gem install jekyll -v 2.5

jekyll serve

To check out the "official" release documentation at h2r.github.io/ein use: 
git clone http://github.com/h2r/ein ein-website
cd ein-website
git checkout gh-pages

However the Ein doc is also duplicated in each checkout and branch so
the way to see the latest doc is to use the doc directory in an ein
checkout and view it by running Jeykll locally.

We chose to use Jekyll because that is what github uses to host a documentation website.



